f=Product/loom/custom/experiment-registry/SKILL.md · in=append-only record experiment verdict: hypothesis, test, frozen criteria, result, adopt/reject decision. company never unknowingly re-runs settled experiment, "we tried that" checkable claim date. · p=Institutional amnesia makes teams re-run last year's failed pricing test re-learn lesson full cost. registry makes experiment history queryable before proposing test, check whether (or near-twin) already verdict. · wu=experiment reaches verdict (experiment-discipline files here)., Before proposing experiment query: run? (the re-run guard)., decision cites "we tested that" registry claim verified exposed. · st:/ Protocol=QUERY-FIRST proposed experiment first checks registry: run before? near-twin? stale-but-relevant?) verdict: SETTLED (cite existing result, don't re-run) STALE (context changed enough re-test say why) NEW FILE (on verdict: hypothesis, test type, frozen criteria `metric:@vN`, result, ADOPT/REJECT, date, confidence append-only, scout's pattern) LINK (which PRDs/features/prices verdict informed) SURFACE (settled verdicts searchable; re-run proposal without stated delta prior test bounces). · in=Query before proposing re-run guard mirrors ux's query-first scout's adopt-reject; re-running settled experiment needs stated reason context changed. Append-only, never edited: superseded verdict stays readable date, "what believe then" answerable (precedent's discipline, experiment edition). Record frozen criteria, result verdict without pre-set decision rule can't trusted reused result whose bar moved noise). ADOPT/REJECT explicit dated "inconclusive" valid third verdict (and prompt design better test), never silent drawer. Link downstream: registry knows which decisions verdict shaped, later-overturned result trace what touched (annealing). · of=Registry entry: experiment hypothesis test frozen criteria (metric@vN) result ADOPT/REJECT/INCONCLUSIVE date confidence informed (PRD/price IDs). Query result: SETTLED/STALE/NEW refs. · pr=Query before you re-run settled experiments cited, repeated., Append-only; verdicts keep their frozen criteria their date., Adopt/reject/inconclusive explicit, never silent drawer. · f=Empty registry (new company)? Query-first still runs (returns NEW honestly); discipline place experiment #1, amnesia never sets in. · b:with Other Skills=experiment-discipline files verdicts here; assumption-mapping's tested beliefs land entries; pmf-scorecard's PMF reads registry-recorded over time., scout (AI Agents) runs adopt-reject pattern marketplace skills; loom's registry product-experiment analogue one pattern, two subjects., spec/price cite registry verdicts evidence ("we tested that, here's result"); anneal consumes overturned verdicts skill lessons.